#doc (Manual) "Signatures, free algebras, ramified types" =>

This chapter is the reference counterpart to Part I chapters 1 and 3: it
renders the declarations of `GebLean/Ramified/AlgSig.lean`,
`GebLean/Ramified/Algebras.lean`, `GebLean/Ramified/SortedSig.lean`, and
`GebLean/Ramified/RType.lean` underlying the vocabulary those chapters
introduce. Each declaration's own doc comment states its content; the prose
here places each in relation to its neighbours.

# Free-algebra signatures

A free-algebra signature names constructor labels with their arities; its
polynomial endofunctor presents that data as a `PolyEndo`, whose `PolyFix`
W-type is the free algebra generated by a single generic constructor.

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.AlgSig}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.AlgSig.polyEndo}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.FreeAlg}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.FreeAlg.mk}

# The recurrence over a free algebra

The recurrence over a free algebra is a paramorphism: its step functions see
the parameters, the subterms of the recurrence argument, and the recursive
results; it reduces at each constructor node to the step function applied to
those three.

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.FreeAlg.recurse}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.FreeAlg.recurse_mk}

