# The polyadic word algebra and the tree algebra

{name GebLean.Ramified.binWordAlgSig}`binWordAlgSig` and
{name GebLean.Ramified.treeAlgSig}`treeAlgSig` are instances of the
{tech}[polyadic word algebra] and {tech}[tree algebra] classes, alongside the
{tech}[monadic word algebra] instance
{name GebLean.Ramified.natAlgSig}`natAlgSig` above. Part I chapter 6 states
complexity readings against the monadic and polyadic classes and explicitly
declines one against the tree-algebra class, on cost-model grounds.

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.binWordAlgSig}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.treeAlgSig}

Each signature's carrier has constructors that build `FreeAlg` values
directly, carrying no r-type sort of their own.

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.binEmpty}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.binCons}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.treeLeaf}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.treeNode}

Each carrier also carries one {tech}[monotonic] recurrence and one
{tech}[flat] recurrence, built from
{name GebLean.Ramified.RIdent}`RIdent`, the schema-identifier type
{name GebLean.Ramified.RIdent.mrec}`RIdent.mrec` and
{name GebLean.Ramified.RIdent.frec}`RIdent.frec` construct — Part II
chapter 4's subject. {name GebLean.Ramified.binLength}`binLength` and
{name GebLean.Ramified.treeSize}`treeSize` are the {tech}[monotonic]
instances; {name GebLean.Ramified.binTail}`binTail` and
{name GebLean.Ramified.treeLeftChild}`treeLeftChild` are the {tech}[flat]
ones. Each is typed at {tech}[object type]s built from the base type: the
monotonic recurrences take their recurrence argument at
`RType.omega RType.o`, the flat ones at `RType.o`, and all four output
`RType.o`.

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.binLength}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.binTail}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.treeSize}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.treeLeftChild}

# Morphisms of free-algebra signatures

A morphism of free-algebra signatures transports one carrier into another
along a {tech}[constructor label] map that preserves arities.

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.AlgSigHom}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.freeAlgMap}

# Multi-sorted signatures

{name GebLean.Ramified.SortedSig}`SortedSig` moves from the single-sorted
free-algebra signatures above to signatures over an explicit sort type, the
format Part II chapter 3's Lawvere-theory layer builds on.
{name GebLean.Ramified.SortedSig.sum}`SortedSig.sum` assembles two
signatures over the same sorts by disjoint union of their operations.
{name GebLean.Ramified.constructorSig}`constructorSig` is the bridge between
the free-algebra and multi-sorted formats: it reads a free-algebra signature
back as a multi-sorted one, with one operation per {tech}[object type] and
{tech}[constructor label].

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.SortedSig}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.SortedSig.sum}

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.constructorSig}

# Ramified types as a free algebra

The {tech}[r-type]s themselves are generated as a free algebra over a
three-label signature, reusing every declaration of the first two
sections at a new instance.

{docstring GebLean.Ramified.RTypeShape}

